job_description:
.NET Architect Position For Your Consideration

Become a member of a growing team of Information Technology professionals making an impact and providing solutions for Government and Commercial clients since 1996 – Join the Domino Tech Team!

The Position:

Client: Commonwealth of Pennsylvania – General Government Delivery Center (GGDC)

Position Title: GGDC – .NET Architect FA1 (723150)

Location: Remote Off-Site with Client in Harrisburg, PA

Duration: Initial term through 06/30/2023 (+ Annual Renewal in 1-Year Terms)

Note: Position is Remote Off-Site, but candidate must report to Harrisburg to receive issued equipment. Candidate must go through CJIS certification in addition to the normal PATCH background check.

The General Government Delivery Center (GGDC) is seeking a .NET Architect to perform the following;

- Provide support to the systems development teams by providing highly technical expertise on various development technologies.

- Participate in design reviews and troubleshooting sessions within various development teams.

- Work with the business and technical resource teams, understand the business requirements and develop technical strategies/solutions that align with business objectives.

- Work with development teams to ensure applications properly adhere to internal and external standards and best practices.

- Create, implement, consume, and maintain Web Service interfaces.

- Provide software architectural assessment and suggest best practices implementation.

- Maintain proper development and support documentations.

The Preferred Skills and Experience:

- 10+ Years: Experience in designing and implementing large and high-performance internet-facing web applications

- 5+ Years: Experience with .NET development combining .NET Core, MVC, C#, ASP.NET, Razor, and associated Web Development tools

- 5+ Years: Development experience with relational database technologies and programming including SQL Server

- Experience with creating, implementing, consuming, and maintaining Web Services

The Company:

The mission of Domino Technologies, Inc. is to provide clients with IT solutions for their individual business processes that lead to strategic market advantages. Since its founding in 1996, the Domino Tech Team has built a solid record of performance working with clients in the Government and Commercial sectors.

The Perks:

- Excellent Market Salary

- Competitive Benefits

- Paid Holidays and Vacation

- Positive Work-Life Balance

The Location:

Domino Technologies is based in the Harrisburg area – the capital city of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania and the county seat of Dauphin County. Located on the east bank of the Susquehanna River, Harrisburg is the anchor of the Susquehanna Valley metropolitan area.

Contact Us Today!

Job Location: Fully Remote

6 Month Contract to Hire (Full time conversion post 6-month contract is preferred)

Job Summary

Brooksource is looking for an experienced BizTalk and .NET developer to join an internal development team focused on application development and business requirement matching. The team they will be allocated to is the Wires Management team as they work to modernize internal enterprise platforms. You will be working on an agile team that is retiring BizTalk and modernizing .NET solutions with significant value in the organization. A developer in this role is ideally coming from an agile environment working within a fast-paced team

Job Requirements
• Ability to work as an independent, proactive, resourceful, cooperative, and respectful team member
• Follow established processes including version control and secure coding standards
• Complete unit testing, including using a de-bugger to identify and correct issues
• Follow agile development practices
• Work with Azure DevOps for task tracking, source control, etc.
• Design, develop, and document new features and bug fixes.

• 4+ Years BizTalk 2016 experience
• 4+ Years C# .NET experience including Framework 4.x and .NET 6+

Additional Skills
